rComments: Young (inexperienced) prof. Good lecturer but could not write exams. Not a good grasp of the knowledge of his students. last midterm avg. was 38%, with a medium of 42. A bunch of students filed official complaints with the dept and the final was much easier.
Brutal problem sets and term tests. Makes the course harder than previous years.

He's nice, funny and extremely intelligent.  However, tests are hard.. Test 1 and 3 were completely WHACK.  Thank god for the bell curve.  I learned a lot though, I feel that my math skill has matured a lot after doing through this course.

...I thought the first two term-tests were alright, but the third term test was completely out of whack... As someone said here, the homework problems are completely useless for preparing for the tests.

Worst instructor ever. He tries to show how smart he is since he went to Stanford for his PhD, this makes everyone feel stupid. The 1st term test is out of the book, out of the lectures, the class avg is about 30%. If you have him, you are out of luck.
I think he's one of the best mat235 prof...plus he's funny=)
